    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s lineup efficiency is anchored today by **Daulton Varsho** (69.94) and **Brendan Donovan** (68.26), who represent our highest-upside plays. **Varsho** benefits from a strong platoon advantage against Bradley, combined with a favorable park factor, while **Donovan** draws a plus-matchup against Bolton, seeing his score ballooned by a significant +14% dynamic platoon boost and a +10% bump for leading off. **Bryson Stott** (68.82) also clears our \"Strong\" threshold comfortably; despite facing a capable arm in Gallen, the favorable platoon environment and a +4% park factor keep him in a prime position to contribute across our target categories.\n\nWhile the algorithm remains high on our primary starters, **Jung Hoo Lee** (53.15) serves as the most notable exclusion from today\u2019s lineup. He narrowly missed the cut behind the superior efficiency projections of **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Lawrence Butler**, both of whom benefit from superior order placement or more favorable park environments. On the risk front, we are closely monitoring **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (55.12). He faces a challenging matchup against Sale, with his base projection suppressed by the elite skill of the opposing pitcher and a mediocre BvP history. While his talent typically warrants an auto-start, his sub-60 score reflects the volatility of betting against an elite southpaw. Finally, **Yainer Diaz** (39.08) was held out specifically to preserve game caps, falling below our 40.0 \"Below Floor\" threshold due to a daunting matchup against Gilbert. We remain cautious with **Matt Chapman** (58.27) as well, as his potential for production is slightly stifled by Povich\u2019s ability to limit stolen base opportunities, a critical variable in our 5x5 Roto calculus.",
